<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Encourage Export of Mechanical, Electrical Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 29 (Xinhua) -- China plans to support the export
of complete sets of mechanical and electrical equipment with
favorable foreign exchange policies.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration of Foreign Exchange will adopt a
series of measures to support the in-depth reform of large and
medium-sized state-owned enterprises, which includes permitting
qualified and well-credited large-scale enterprises and groups to
directly circulate funds from overseas.
</P>
<P>
The administration also plans to urge large-sized enterprise
groups to invest and set up factories abroad, taking up foreign
markets, according to a source at the administration.
</P>
<P>
The country will support banks to engage in export credit
business, especially to give buyers' credit, and will encourage
export of complete sets of mechanical and electrical equipment to
Southeast Asia, Latin America, and Africa, the source said.
</P>
</TEXT>
