<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Abolish Tariffs on Non-Alcoholic Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, March 29 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian government today
decided to abolish tariffs on all imports except alcohol, state
television reported.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at boosting production in the country,
according to an instruction President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat gave
the government Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ochirbat said that tariffs had become a barrier to
restoring production, and a factor in pushing prices upward, when
enterprises suffered from a shortage of raw materials and large
debts.
</P>
<P>
The country's economy began to decline late last year, and the
fall has yet to be stopped.
</P>
<P>
The resolution must be approved by the Great Hural (parliament)
in early April before it can come into force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
