<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Communist Party Leader Reiterates Renovation Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's Communist Party leader Do
Muoi today reaffirmed the country's determination to
pursue its "renovation," or reform, policies.
</P>
<P>
Addressing some 800 high-ranking officials from both central
and local government, the General Secretary said Vietnam's
multi-sector socialist-oriented economic policies aimed to
continue improving the material and spiritual lives of Vietnamese
people.
</P>
<P>
"In parallel with the policy to ensure the leading role of the
state-owned economic sector, the state encourages the growth of
other economic sectors, increasing joint ventures and integration
between different economic sectors," he told officials attending a
training course to study the resolutions of the Eighth National
Party Congress. 
</P>
