<HEADLINE> Singapore Wants Good Ties With Malaysia: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong said today that his country wants "good relations" with
Malaysia and will do its part to restore and improve cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued tonight, Goh said, "I welcome Dr
Mahathir's assurance that media reports of a Malaysian cabinet
decision to freeze Malaysia-Singapore relations are not true."
</P>
<P>
"I am saddened that our bilateral relations have been upset by
Senior Minister's remarks on Johor," he said, noting that Senior
Minister Lee Kuan Yew had said that it was never his intention to
cause offense.
</P>
<P>
In fact, the prime minister said, Lee Kuan Yew had immediately
apologized to him when the remarks became public.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that closer cooperation between Malaysia and
Singapore will benefit both countries. We will do our part to
restore and improve cooperation at a pace Malaysia is comfortable
with," Goh promised.
</P>
<P>
"We want good relations with Malaysia and my remarks on 25
March were intended to be helpful and to improve relations," he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
