<HEADLINE> Rubbish Trade Fair Opens in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 29 (Xinhua) -- The first ever "Rubbish Trade
Fair" opened in Angola's capital of Luanda today as a prelude to
the country's national sanitation week with its theme as "the
cleaner, the healthier".
</P>
<P>
The campaign, initiated by several non-governmental
organizations, was aimed at building Angola into a clean, healthy
country, said organizers.
</P>
<P>
Different types of tractors, dustbins, cleaning machines and
photos were on the show. 
</P>
