<HEADLINE> Nigerians Warned of Possible Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lagos, March 29 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian Ministry of Water and
Resources has raised an alarm of an impending drought in many parts of
the country, particularly those areas that are yet to experience
rainfall since mid-1996, the Saturday Champion reported today.
</P>
<P>
Water Minister Alhaji Jibrin Yelwa was quoted as saying on Friday that
unless safety measures were put in place, a major starvation would
befall the country.
</P>
<P>
"By the cycle of drought in the West African sub-region, we expect
a major drought in the next seven years with attendant negative
consequencies witnessed between 1973 and 1975," the minister told a
national seminar on irrigation.
</P>
<P>
Irrigation schemes in all parts of the country have become a
necessity, he said, urging both governments and individuals to assist
in the provisions, reservation and protection of water for the life of
future generations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
