<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Punishes 55 Foreigners for Violating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's security,
immigration and refugees affairs authority announced today that a
total of 55 foreigners violating immigration rules during the
second half of last year have been fined, among whom nine were
expelled from the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the foreigners, who
were from 21 countries spreading over almost all the continents,
were fined and expelled because they illegally entered Ethiopia
and failed to renew visas and residence permits.
</P>
<P>
The authority said those who were expelled from the country
could never re-enter Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 32 tourists whose visas expired were similarly
fined and get their visas renewed just to fly back home. And 14
other resident foreigners who failed to renew their residence
permits in time have also been fined but later get their permits
renewed.
</P>
<P>
There are over 8,000 resident foreigners engaged in various
disciplines all over Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
