<HEADLINE> Palestinian University Student Killed by Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 29 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian university
student was killed by Israeli soldiers during an anti-Israeli
demonstration in the West Bank this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Khalil Abdullah, 20, a second-year engineering
student at Bir zeit University near Ramallah, was shot in the
back by live bullets during clashes on the road between
Jerusalem and Ramallah, according to a report of JMCC, a
Palestinian press service based in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The clashes took place close to an Israeli military
checkpoint on the road. Dozens of university students were
protesting against Israeli construction of a new Jewish
settlement at Har Homa in East Jerusalem. The student was from
Beit Sahur, a Palestinian town close to Har Homa.
</P>
<P>
The fatal incident will apparently add fuel to the flames of
the anger of the Palestinians stemming from the settlement
building and the subsequent violent crackdown on the Palestinian
protesters. A wave of intifada-type Palestinian opposition has
surged in the West Bank for more than a week.
</P>
<P>
It also came one day after U.S. Middle East envoy Dennis Ross
failed to bridge the gap of differences between the Israelis and
Palestinins over revival of the peace process during his two-day
talks with Palestinian President Yasser Arafat in Morocco and
Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu in Israel
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
