<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Security Forces Find 500 Kg Bomb in Norther Ireland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Britain's security forces found a
1,000 pound (500 kilogram) bomb and detonating equipment today
near a British army base in County Down, south of Belfast,
Northern Ireland, according to a BBC television report.
</P>
<P>
The device was found on the road near the base in Ballykinler,
where a spokesman said army vehicles would have been forced to
slow down and the bomb only needed to be connected up to make it
lethal.
</P>
<P>
The homemade explosives were discovered in fertilizer bags, and
a Kalashnakov assault rifle was found nearby.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was thought to be planted by the Irish Republican Army
guerrillas to try to make headlines in the running-up to Britain's
general election due on May 1.
</P>
<P>
No one has so far claimed responsibility for it, but police
said that the attempt bore the hallmarks of the IRA, which is
fighting British rule in Northern Ireland and has carried out a
series of bomb attacks in the country since February 1996 when it
ended a 17-month cease-fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
