<HEADLINE> 7th All African Trade Fair Opens in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KADUNA, Nigeria, March 29 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh All African
Trade and Tourism Fair, jointly sponsored by the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) and African Economic Community (AEC), opened
today in Nigeria's northern industrial city of Kaduna.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant-General Oladipo Diya, vice-chairman of the
Nigeria's Provisional Ruling Council, declared the fair open
representing Head of State General Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
OAU Secretary-General Salim Ahmed Salim, Nigerien President
Ibrahim Bare Mainassara and Chadian Prime Minister Djimasta
Koibla were among the dignitaries attending opening ceremony at
the newly-built Kaduna International Trade Complex, an impressive
building that has cost 12.5 billion Naira (15 million U.S.
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Also present are Nigerian government officials and business
leaders as well as foreign diplomats.
</P>
<P>
In a keynote speech today, Nigerian Minister of Commerce and
Tourism Rear Admiral Jibrila Ayinla warned that African countries
now face the danger of being left out of the globalization of the
world economy and urged them to strengthen regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to organizers, more than 30 countries will display
their various products at the fair that will last until April 6.
</P>
<P>
However, due to the delay in the completion of the
construction of the trade fair complex, most of the firms were
not able to bring in their goods before the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the fair is to "promote African development, buy
African goods and tour Africa."
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that tourism is promoted as a major theme
of All Africa Trade Fair, an event held once every four years.
</P>
<P>
The Kaduna fair will be the last regional comprehensive trade
fair in the African continent in this century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
