<HEADLINE> Switzerland, Scotland Win Titles in World Junior Curling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, MARCH 30 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland beat Finland 5-3 for
the men's title Sunday, while Scotland trounced Sweden 11-3 for
the women's gold in the World Junior Curling Championships in
Karuizawa, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Ralph Stockli's Swiss curlers were never seriously threatened
throughout nine ends of a scheduled 10-end game after Stockli
scored a quick two points in the first.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss team allowed Perttu Piilo's Finnish team only three
points through the ninth, while Stockli scored three more,
blanking ends to keep the last-rock advantage.
</P>
<P>
In the women's final, Scotland overwhelmed Sweden in eight ends.
</P>
<P>
Scotland was runner-up to Canada in the last championships,
held in Red Deer, Alberta, Canada.
</P>
<P>
In the men's competition, Canada placed third and Japan
fourth. In the women's, Canada finished third and the United
States fourth.
</P>
<P>
Curling will make its Olympic debut as a full medal event at
this Kazakoshi Park Arena in the Nagano Winter Games next
February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
