<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Hails Sino-French Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qiao Shi said that to build a strong, prosperous, democratic
and highly civilized socialist country is the objective of a
struggle for China.
</P>
<P>
He said that Deng Xiaoping had pointed out years ago that if
there was no democracy, there would be no socialism and socialist
modernization.
</P>
<P>
"In order to protect and guarantee the democracy of the people,
we must strengthen the construction of a legal system. We must
institutionalize our democracy and make it into law, so that the
democratic system and law will not be subjected to changes due to
changes of the country's leaders or their views and attention," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that since the country's reform and opening-up began
nearly 20 years ago, China has followed the thoughts of Deng
Xiaoping in this respect and regarded the building-up of socialist
democracy as a basic task for the country.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the NPC has since then taken a series of
important measures to achieve this end, including the making of
the 1982 Constitution, the reforms of electoral system, the making
and amending of the Criminal Code, the Criminal Procedural Law,
the Administrative Procedural Law, and the Law on State
Compensation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the NPC has also strengthened the autonomy in the
running of rural villages and urban neighborhoods by inhabitants
of villages and cities with the adoption of the draft law on
election of village-level administrative bodies and that on
election of urban neighborhood administrative bodies.
</P>
<P>
Those laws have helped improve the building-up of democracy at
the grass roots level of the Chinese society, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
