<HEADLINE> Army Rockets Becomes National Basketball Champions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Army Rockets became China's
national basketball champions for the 1996-1997 season on Sunday
after overwhelming Liaoning Hunters 102-66 in the second game of
the finals.
</P>
<P>
Li Nan, who shot 5 of 6 for three pointers, scored 29 points to
help Rockets dominate throughout the game in Shenyang,
northeastern Liaoning Province. Rockets, who won the first game
87-69, led the first half 58-37.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yudong added 27 points, Zhang Jingsong had 18 and Wang
Zhizhi scored 15 as five Rockets players registered double-digit
figures.
</P>
<P>
American Jim Havbilla led Liaoning with 14 points. Wu Naiqun
added 10.
</P>
<P>
Rockets coach Wang Fei said, "We were great on offence and
rebounds tonight. Hunters only had 66 points, which proved that
our defence was good, too."
</P>
<P>
Liaoning coach Li Ge said, "We were quite late in buying
foreign players this year and slow in starting. But after that we
won 17 straight games."
</P>
<P>
In Jinan, eastern Shandong Province, Guangdong Tigers lost
squandered a 44-31 first-half lead before losing to Shandong
Flaming Bulls 78-79 but still finished third in the league.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, who won the first game 100-68 at home, lost steam at
the second half only to see Shandong levelled the score 78-78 after
converting three consecutive free throws.
</P>
<P>
Shandong won the game after being awarded another free throw
after a Guangdong player interfered with Shandong's earlier
throwing from the line. 
</P>
