<HEADLINE> Over 100,000 Motor Vehicles Stocked in South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 30 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's major automakers have
more than 100,000 vehicles in stock due to poor car sales, Yonhap
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Car sales of the country's three biggest automakers -- Hyundai,
Kia and Daewoo -- were 50,000, 25,000 and 25,000 respectively this
month, only sixty to seventy percent of that projected.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the motor vehicle stock has reached
109,000 to 110,000 by March 27, 20,000 more than the 85,000
vehicles in stock last month, according to the International Trade
and Industry Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The rising stock will increase the costs of storage and slow
the turnover of capital. It is estimated that the automakers
suffer 340,000,000 won (over 382,000 U.S. dollars) per day for the
110,000 motor vehicles in stock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
