<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police are
investigating a robbery case in which more than one million HK
dollars in cash was snatched by four armed robbers in Sheung Shui
Saturday night, a police spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, three security guards last night
returned to their van parked near Sheung Shui Kowloon-Guangzhou
Railway Station after they got 1.05 million HK dollars there.
</P>
<P>
When they opened the van's door, three culprits, armed with two
 pistol-like-objects, approached them. The money in a box was
later snatch by the culprits after a brief clash between them.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a fourth culprit, also armed with a
pistol-like-object, pushed a driver out of his private car parked
near the van, and fled with his accomplices towards the direction
of Kai Leng.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that no one was injured, nor any gun shot
was fired in the incident.
</P>
<P>
He said the robbery was well-organized and the case was still
under investigation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
