<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Hails Sino-French Relations in Spring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) of China, today
hailed the Sino-French relations in spring, saying that he was
happy to visit France in this beautiful season full of hope and
life.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Alain Peyrefitte, chairman of the
editorial board of the French daily Le Figaro, Qiao said that both
China and France have an ancient history and boast a brilliant
civilization, and the people of the two countries enjoy a long
traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that late Chinese leaders Zhou Enlai and Deng
Xiaoping studied and worked in France in their youths, and that
period of life of theirs had exerted a great impact on their
revolutionary careers.
</P>
<P>
He said that through his meetings with President Jacques
Chirac, Prime Minister Alain Juppe, Senate President Rene Monory
and National Assembly President Philippe Seguin, China and France
have enhanced mutual understanding, strengthened friendship and
expanded cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that the NPC and its standing committee have a great
responsibility for the cause of reform and opening-up, the
building of a socialist market economy and the construction of a
socialist state with a sound legal system in China.
</P>
<P>
He said that China needs to learn from the successful
experience of all countries in the world while starting from its
own actual situation.
</P>
<P>
He said that to further strengthen the friendly relations
between the NPC and the French parliament will be helpful for the
NPC to understand and study the experience in law-making by the
French parliament.
</P>
<P>
Qiao stressed that Sino-French relations are very important,
and that it will not only benefit the development of China and
France, but also world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government and people are looking
forward to the forthcoming visit by President Jacques Chirac to
China, and expressed his confidence that Sino-French relations
will surely be further developed through the joint efforts by both
countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
