<HEADLINE> Special Trains to Start Operation in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Special passenger trains with
upgraded services will be put into operation on the railways
connecting Shanghai and Nanjing on April 1.
</P>
<P>
Each train has three types of carriages, including a 42-seat
top-class car, three 68-seat first-class cars, and 11 second-class
cars with 88 seats each.
</P>
<P>
Passengers in the top-class and first-class carriages will be
provided with free drinks and daily newspapers, and two rooms in
the first-class car will be available for use as temporary offices.
</P>
<P>
There will be two such trains on the route between Nanjing and
Shanghai, another two on the route between Changzhou and Shanghai,
another two between Wuxi and Shanghai and one for the journey from
Shanghai to Suzhou.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two special trains will be put into operation on the
railways connecting Shanghai and Hangzhou, which will be on the
route between Suzhou and Ningbo and the route between Ningbo and
Shanghai respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
