<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Beats Thailand in World Cup Asian Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong defeated Thailand 3-2
 after the two teams tied 1-1 at half-time in a World Cup soccer
Asian Zone Group Six qualifying match here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Although with the victory Hong Kong could revenged its 2-0 loss
 to Thailand earlier this month, it could hardly change the fact
that South Korea will eventually come out as the group
winners. Neither could it save Hong Kong from being at the bottom
of the group standings.
</P>
<P>
South Korea, with two straight wins in earlier competitions,
3-1 over Thailand and 2-0 over Hong Kong, led the group standings
with an almost unbeatable collection of six points.
</P>
<P>
With two games left, against Hong Kong and Thailand, both on
the home turf, South Korea need only a tie to win the three-team
group.
</P>
<P>
Both Hong Kong and Thailand now stand at three points, from one
 win and one loss each.
</P>
<P>
With little hope to go into the next round though, Hong Kong
played an surprisingly aggressive game today and, with a
short-passing coordination just 21 minutes into the match, opened
the score through a slam shot by forward Lee Kin Wo.
</P>
<P>
Thailand evened the score 23 minutes later when Natipong scored
 a goal in a goal mouth melee following a corner-kick.
</P>
<P>
The hosts scored two more goals in the second half while the
Thai side added just one.
</P>
<P>
But the match was marred by what Kwok Ka Ming called as an
"incident", followed by the expulsion of one player from each
side, in the closing minute of the first half.
</P>
<P>
Scorers:
</P>
<P>
For Hong Kong: Lee Kin Wo (21st Minute), Cheng Siu Chung
(48th), Au Wai Lun (89th)
</P>
<P>
For Thailand: Natipong (44th), Dusit (69th)
</P>
</TEXT>
