<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank of Communications Donates for Charity, Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- China's Shanghai-based Bank of
Communications has donated one million yuan to the Shanghai
Charity Foundation as a way to celebrate the bank's 10th
anniversary of reorganization on April 1.
</P>
<P>
BOC's Shanghai Branch also donated one million yuan to an
education foundation to mark the occasion. The branch has donated a
total of 8.5 million yuan in support of social welfare since it
opened 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The donations are meant to repay the city and the society at
large for their consistent support to the bank, said Wang
Mingquan, the bank's chairman.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1908, the Bank of Communications is one of the
oldest banks in China. In 1958, its mainland businesses were
merged into the People's Bank of China and the Construction Bank
of China, while its Hong Kong Branch remains open under the
original name.
</P>
<P>
The State Council decided in 1986 to reorganize the Bank of
Communications to cater to economic development and financial
system reforms. It restarted operation the next year.
</P>
<P>
The bank has been transformed into a shareholding commercial
bank, with a total capital worth nearly 400 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Charity Foundation, set up in 1994, has received
more than 100 million yuan of charity donations from home and
abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
