<HEADLINE> 17 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in operations in
southeastern Turkey launched by the Turkish security forces, an
official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the security forces wiped out 12 PKK militants in
Yolcati village of Lice town in Diyarbakir province, three in
Nusaybin town of Mardin province and two in Eruh town of Siirt
province.
</P>
<P>
It said that one PKK guerrilla surrendered to the security
forces in Silopi town of Sirnak province bordering northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the security forces also captured some weapons from
the PKK during the operations, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The security forces are continuing their operations in a bid to
wipe out the PKK militants in this region where the PKK has been
fighting a 12-year-old guerrilla war for autonomy, which has
claimed more than 21,000 lives in the conflicts between the
security forces and the PKK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
