<HEADLINE> 1,000 People Plant Commemorative Trees In Suburban Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The site of China's first
"Wedding and Happiness Memory Forest," located in suburban
Beijing's Huairou County, was filled with some 1,000
commemorative tree-planters today.
</P>
<P>
While couples planted trees to mark their wedding day, people
from the business, scientific, and music circles as well as
students and government employees planted trees to show their good
wishes for the future.
</P>
<P>
A female employee from the Beijing-based People's Bank of
China, who planted a "Return of Hong Kong Tree" today with her
family, said she was excited about the event.
</P>
<P>
"We planted the tree to show our pride and joy over the return
of Hong Kong later this year, hoping that Hong Kong will always be
full of vitality, just like the tree we planted," she said.
</P>
<P>
She said the tree also symbolizes her feelings for late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping, who advocated the nation's tree-planting
drive 16 years ago and initiated the "one country two systems"
policy which made the return of Hong Kong possible.
</P>
<P>
The "Wedding and Happiness Memory Forest," initiated by Chen
Muhua, Vice-Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress and president of the Green China Fund, was
officially opened last October when the first commemorative trees
were planted.
</P>
<P>
The forest covers an area of 178 hectares, space enough for
more than 50,000 trees.
</P>
<P>
Chen and officials from the Ministry of Forestry, the Green
China Fund, the All-China Women's Federation, and Beijing
municipal government, attended today's event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
