<HEADLINE> Beijing to Improve Technology Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Since 1991, Beijing has witnessed
speedy and stable development in its local technology market,
which is believed to be the largest of its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese capital now has 56 technology trading
organizations, and signed nearly 4.6 billion yuan worth of
contracts last year, 80 percent of which were for technological
trade.
</P>
<P>
This is a big leap from the two billion yuan-worth of
technological contracts signed in 1991, when only 60 percent
involved technological trade.
</P>
<P>
In order to upgrade technology transfer, Beijing took the lead
in China to hold two terms of training courses for professional
technological agents.
</P>
<P>
Beijing set up a comprehensive and multi-functional
technological trading market last year, which is expected to
provide all-round services and have become an important site for
the exchange and trading of local technological information and
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
