<HEADLINE> Chinese Taxation Policy Supports Overseas Listing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Nine Chinese companies which have
listed shares in Hong Kong will continue to enjoy preferential tax
policies in 1997.
</P>
<P>
A circular from the Ministry of Finance and the State
Administration of Taxation stipulated that the government will
impose 15 percent less on the earnings tax on the nine H Share
companies, including Shanghai Petrochemicals and Qingdao Beer.
</P>
<P>
Proceeds from social welfare lotteries were also tax-exempt,
according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
Credit cooperatives in impoverished rural areas and the China
Gold Coin Corporation will also continue to be exempt from the
earnings tax, the circular said.  
