<HEADLINE> China to Be World's Largest Elevator Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to become the
world's largest elevator market with an annual demand of 400,000
by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
At present, China has the capacity of producing 30,000
elevators a year, ranking third in the world. The market demand
grows at an annual rate of 10 percent, said Li Zhendong, vice
minister of construction.
</P>
<P>
Kone Corporation in Finland, one of the three largest elevator
companies in the world, is to build a joint venture in east China's
Jiangsu Province with an investment of 29 million US dollars. It
will turn out 1,600 elevators upon its completion in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
