<HEADLINE> Tibet to Put 400 Million Yuan in Telecom Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Tibet Autonomous Region has decided
to invest 400 million yuan (about 50 million dollars) in its major
telecommunications projects.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the telecommunications
department, the major telecom projects include laying optical
fiber lines from Lanzhou in Gansu Province to Xining, from Qinghai
Province to Lhasa, Tibet, from Nyingchi to Qamdo and from Nyingchi
to Mainling.
</P>
<P>
The official said Tibet is also to launch projects on a
regional TV conference system, the Lhasa digital telephone
network, the analog telephone networks in Shannan, Xigaze and
Nyingchi, as well as the technical upgrading of the Lhasa mobile
telecommunications system and the regional pager systems.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Tibet is to complete the construction of an
emergency telecommunications network and its headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The official said Tibet is to add 30,000 phone lines this year
and telephone coverage rate in Tibet's urban and township areas is
expected to reach 12.5 percent, and 20.5 percent in Lhasa, by the
end of the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
