<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 200-year-old Envelope for Confidential Letter Found in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- County archives in east China's
Fujian Province has collected from a local farmer a 200-year-old
envelope for a confidential letter.
</P>
<P>
The letter, sent on March 12, 1776, was from a county governor
in northwest China's Gansu Province to the governor of the
Shanghang County in Fujian where the envelope was found.
</P>
<P>
The envelope, made of white writing paper made from bamboo, is
35 cm long and 19 cm wide, with its covers on the upper and lower
ends of the facade.
</P>
<P>
The addresses and names of the receiver and sender were written
vertically from the right to the left.
</P>
<P>
Seals of the sender can be found on the cover edges and on the
date on the back of the envelope.
</P>
<P>
Experts, determining that the envelope was for a confidential
letter, say that the find will contribute to the study of the
history of posts, especially for the sending of confidential
papers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
