<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Better Sino-Japanese Ties (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan should draw on
historical experience in a bid to jointly create a brighter future
at this important moment for developing Sino-Japanese relations,
President Jiang Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
This is an important moment for both countries to inherit the
past and forge towards the future as they mark the 25th
anniversary of the normalization of diplomatic ties between them
this year and the 20th anniversary of the signing of the
Sino-Japanese Peace and Friendship Treaty next year, Jiang told
visiting Japanese Foreign Minister Ikeda Yukihiko during a meeting
today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reviewed his meeting with Prime Minister Hashimoto in
Manila last November and described it as being "positive and
fruitful", saying that they reached some important common
understanding on how to develop bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"Recently I had the chance to converse with several visiting
Japanese statesmen, and they also expressed the strong desire to
further promote Sino-Japanese friendship, and I feel happy and
gratified with this," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Ikeda said he held in-depth talks with Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen yesterday, and both agreed to further
build a stable relationship between the two countries at a time
when they celebrate the 25th anniversary of the normalization of
Sino-Japanese diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese side will properly handle the problems cropping up
in bilateral ties by strictly adhering to the principles set forth
in the joint declaration and the treaty for peace and friendship,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
Japan, well aware of the significance of its friendship with
China towards the peace and stability of Asia and the world, is
willing to make unremitting efforts in this regard, and continue
to support China's reform, opening up and modernization drive as
well as its bid for the entry to the WTO.
</P>
<P>
China has always put great emphasis on its relations with
Japan, a close neighbor of China, Jiang said, reiterating that it
is very important to adhere to the principles enshrined in the
joint declaration and the peace and friendship treaty, in order to
ensure the healthy and stable development of bilateral ties.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970330.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Better Sino-Japanese Ties (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese and Japanese people had maintained friendly exchanges
for some 2,000 years, however, the aggression by Japanese
militarists against China brought grave disasters to the Chinese
people, and at the same time made Japanese people suffer.
</P>
<P>
"I often tell my Japanese friends the Chinese old sayings
that 'the past experience, if not forgotten, can serve as guide
for the future', and 'the overturned cart ahead is a warning to the
ones behind'," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The historical experience and lessons should be often learnt
from, and this is not only the oriental philosophical concept, but
also a responsibility, he noted, adding we should educate the
young generation to keep the past history in mind and to carry
forward the friendship from generation to generation.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the issue of Taiwan, Jiang said, the crux of the
issue is that foreign countries should not interfere in China's
internal affairs by taking any actions which will harm the
reunification of China and hurt the feelings of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Ikeda reaffirmed the Japanese government's deep retrospection
and sincere apology over its history of aggression, pledging that
this position will never change.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Taiwan, he noted that Japan will adhere to the
"One China" policy and hopes that the two sides across the straits
will settle the issue of reunification peacefully.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan are both countries of great influence in the
region and the world, Jiang said, and to develop the friendly
neighliness and promote their mutual beneficial co-operation not
only conform to the fundamental interests of the two countries
but also constitutes an important and positive factor to the peace,
stability and development of the region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
"Especially at this historical juncture when we are greeting
the coming of the 21st century, how to substantially promote the
friendship between the two countries and contribute more to the
peace and progress of the mankind is not only a historical mission
of the two countries and the two peoples but also an important and
practical task we are facing," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he added, both countries, their state leaders in
particular, should treat and consider bilateral relations from a
far-sighted perspective and a strategic height, and to assure a
correct orientation for the development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, Japanese Ambassador
to China Yoshiyasu Sato were present at today's meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
