<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PNA to Present Draft Resolution on Jerusalem to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 29 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) will present a draft resolution to the ongoing meeting of
the Arab League Council calling for the preservation of Jerusalem
from Israel's Judaization attempts, Xinhua learned today.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting, which drew 18 Arab foreign ministers and
opened at the Arab League headquarters here earlier today, is
expected to focus on Jerusalem, the core and crux of the
Palestinian cause, as an Israeli housing project in East Jerusalem
has sparked 10 days of Palestinian riots and put the peace process
in jeopardy.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians, who claim Jerusalem as a future capital, accused
Israel of aiming through Jewish settlement to cut Arab East
Jerusalem from the Palestinian territories in the West Bank and
preempt talks on a final peace accord that settles the
Palestinian-Israeli issue.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian draft resolution, which might be adopted by the
council, includes a denunciation of the Israeli government
decision to start building the new Jewish settlement in Jabal Abu
Ghneim (Har Homa), East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution calls for sustained Arab and Muslim
coordination in taking appropriate measures to thwart any Israeli
plans concerning East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution calls on the U.N. and other concerned
international quarters to pressure Israel into lifting the ban on
Palestinians to work inside Israel and allow Palestinians, whether
Muslims or Christians, to perform their religious rituals at the
holy site in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution supports the recommendations issued by the
Jerusalem Committee in Morocco last week on setting up a Jerusalem
fund at the disposal of the Palestine Liberation Organization
(PLO) and the PNA in order to confront the Judaization attempts.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian draft resolution also urges a wide-scale
propaganda campaign to confront and shatter Israeli policies,
which are aimed at stripping the Palestinians of their rights to
enjoy a peaceful life on their own soil.
</P>
<P>
It suggests that Jerusalem day be observed on June 28, the day
Israel announced the annexation of East Jerusalem in 1967.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution highlights and emphasizes the Arab
identity of Jerusalem and calls for enabling foreign delegations
to visit the holy city and call on Orient House, PLO's major
representative office in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The draft document welcomes the European Union's statement that
censures Israel's controversial Jewish housing project and eggs on
Russia and the U.S. to force Israel to abide by U.N. Security
Council resolutions 252 and 476 adopted respectively in 1968 and
1980, which considered all Israeli measures in East Jerusalem as
null and void.
</P>
<P>
It entrusts the Arab League Secretary General Esmat
Abdul-Meguid with contacting regional and international
organizations to "pore over the best means and measures through
which the civilizational, cultural, and religious legacy of the
holy city be preserved." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970330.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Congress Stakes Bid to Form New Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- India's Congress party
announced today that it was staking its bid to form a new
government following withdrawal of its support to the 10-month
United Front government led by Prime Minister H.D. Deve Gowda,
Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Congress party President
Sitaram Kesri said Prime Minister Deve Gowda should resign and the
Congress party should get an opportunity to form the government.
</P>
<P>
The letter formally staking the party's bid to form a new
government is being presented to President S.D. Sharma this noon,
the All Indian Congress Committee general secretary, Ghulam Nabi
Azad, said. 
</P>
