<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Congress Chief Submits Letter to President on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Indian Congress Party President
Sitaram Kesri today submitted a letter to President S.D. Sharma,
withdrawing the party's support to the 14-party coalition
government headed by Deve Gowda.
</P>
<P>
In his letter, the Congress president charged the United Front
government with failing to isolate the communal forces and
strengthening the secular forces.
</P>
<P>
The United Front had promised the Congress Party that it would
take all steps to ensure that the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP),
the major opposition in the country, was contained but it failed
in its mission, said Tariq Anwar, political secretary to the party
president.
</P>
<P>
It is due to the United Front's failure, the BJP-Bahujan Samaj
Party had come to power in Uttar Pradesh state, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the last ten months, the Congress had been warning the
ruling United Front but it paid little heed to its demands, he
further said.
</P>
<P>
A crucial meeting of the Congress Working Committee, the
highest policy-making body of the party, is expected shortly to
chalk out the future course of action, Congress Party sources
indicated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
