<HEADLINE> Arab Trade Unions Blasts Israeli Settlement in E. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The International Federation of
Arab Trade Unions (IFATU) denounced today Israel's persistence in
adopting the policy of confiscating Arab lands and setting up new
Jewish settlements in East Jerusalem in an attempt to Judaize the
holy city.
</P>
<P>
This came in a statement issued by the General Secretariat of
the IFATU on the occasion of the Palestinian Land Day, which falls
on March 30.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the IFATU general secretariat expressed its
support for the Palestinian people in their struggle for the
restoration of their just and legitimate rights of repatriation,
self-determination and the establishment of an independent
Palestinian state with Jerusalem as its capital.
</P>
<P>
The statement also appealed to the Arab governments and popular
organizations as well as trade unions across the world to prop up
the Palestinian people in the just struggle to restore their
rights.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, it called for all kinds of pressure on
Israel to force it to give up the Jewish settlement
construction. It also urged Israel to stop the practices of
confiscating Arab land and Judaizing Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
