<HEADLINE> French Police Arrest 30 in Anti-FN Protest in Strasbourg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 30 (Xinhua) -- French police arrested about 30
people, some of them German anarchists, in a clash between police
and demonstrators protesting against the French extreme right
National Front party Saturday night in Strasbourg.
</P>
<P>
The clash took place following a gigantic demonstration against
the extreme-right National Front party earlier in the day, in
which at least 5,000 people took part.
</P>
<P>
The clash began in the evening when some demonstrators broke
several display windows of shops, the window of a bank and some
windows of houses, Agence France-Presse (AFP) reported.
</P>
<P>
The protesters also threw stones at police, wounding lightly
three of them, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
Later at night, a small group of young men also burned a
vehicle of the security force near the central Kleber square of
Strasbourg, where a concert was taking place.
</P>
<P>
These young men also broke windows and looted shops, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
The anti-riot police of Republican Company of Security called
in reinforcement and ordered the protesters to immediately leave
the square at 23:00 (2200 GMT). But around 500 people defied
police order and continued to stay on the square.
</P>
<P>
Police then used water cannon and tear gas to disperse the
demonstrators, and formed a cordon around the square to prevent
protesters from gathering again on the square. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
