<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unicom Opens Digital Mobile Phone Network in Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- United Telecom (Unicom), the sole
authorized telecom competitor of the Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications, opened a sophisticated digital mobile phone
network in Shijiazhuang, capital of Hebei Province, on March 10.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the city of Shijiazhuang, the 130 GSM (global
service for mobile communication) service of Unicom will also
extend to other cities in the province, including Tangshan,
Baoding and Handan, by this summer, the latest issue of
Communications Weekly has reported.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, Unicom will complete a SDH digital microwave
transmission trunk between Handan and Qinhuangdao, a harbor city
north of Beijing, and launch an automatic roaming service among
seven cities in the region.
</P>
