sector participation in infrastructure development and promote
financial and capital market development.
</P>
<P>
During their Subic meeting last November, APEC leaders called
on their finance ministers to pursue concrete and practical
measures to accelerate the development of domestic financial and
capital markets in the region, and stimulate the private sector
participation in infrastructure development.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government said that Michel Camdessus, managing
director of the International Monetary Fund and Mitsuo Sato,
president of the Asian Development Bank will attend the meeting,
at which Philippine President Fidel Ramos will make a key-note
speech.
</P>
<P>
APEC groups Australia, Brunei, Canada, Chile, China, Hong Kong,
Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, Mexico, New Zealand,
Papua New Guinea, the Philippines, Singapore, Chinese Taipei,
Thailand, and the United States. 
