<HEADLINE> S. Africa Deports 14,600 Zimbabweans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 30 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has deported over
14,600 Zimbabweans who were illegally residing there while over
9,000 aspiring visitors had their visa applications turned down
as Pretoria clamps down on illegal aliens.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Mail today quoted the South African High Commission
as saying that out of the 151,585 illegal aliens apprehended in
that country between January and October last year, 28,124 were
Zimbabweans coming second to Mozambique which had over 100,000.
</P>
<P>
During 1995, approximately 63,000 Zimbabweans who entered
South Africa with valid visas did not return, the commission said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
However, despite the introduction of new tougher visa
regulations, only three percent of 312,132 visa applications made
by Zimbabweans were turned down.
</P>
<P>
South African High Commissioner to Zimbabwe Kingsley Mamabolo
told the newspaper that the new visa regulations were not just
for Zimbabwe but for Africa and the whole world. 
</P>
