<HEADLINE> Indian Capital to Launch New Cancer Control Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The government of New Delhi,
capital of India, plans to launch a cancer control program from
March 31, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to statistical data available here, cancer is the
fifth leading cause of death in the capital. There are an
estimated 10,500 suffering from cancer and nearly 1.5 million to
1.8 million people are at the risk of developing the disease in
the city.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the program is aimed at detecting the
disease in early stages, the same sources said, adding that it
would also aim at reducing risk behavior activities like smoking,
drinking and tobacco among the public.
</P>
<P>
Cancer of cervix, uterus, breast, larynx and lungs are most
common in the city, comprising 70-80 percent of the cases.
</P>
<P>
The program is being launched with the special emphasis on
cancer of the above mentioned organs.  
</P>
