<HEADLINE> Art Theft Serious in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, March 29 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 pieces of
religious art works have been stolen during the last five years in
Colombia, the Colcultura Mobile Patrimony Section said.
</P>
<P>
In Fontibon, several men armed with submachine guns entered the
church and took away 12 pieces of art works, one of them a Miguel
de Figueroa oil painting (1830) titled "The Circumcision of Our
Lord."
</P>
<P>
On February 26, 1993, robbers stole the painting "Samson and
the Lion" and a dozen paintings of colonial era painter Baltazar
de Vargas after tying to a chair priest Carlos Gabriel Perez in
the La Pena sanctuary of Bogota.
</P>
<P>
"Many valuable treasures of our cultural patrimony have gone
out of the country because the thieves go through customs with
their booty in hand-held bags without the control of any
authority," said Maria Isabel Gomez, chief of the Colcultura
Mobile Patrimony Section's documentation department. 
</P>
