<HEADLINE> Italy to Make Effort to Restore Peace in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rome, March 29 (Xinhua)-- Italy remains committed to making
every effort to restore peace in Albania, Foreign Minister
Lamberto Dini said in a message of condolence to his Albanian
counterpart following the disaster in the Otranto Channel last
night.
</P>
<P>
Dini expressed his condolences on the part of the Italian
government to Albania and the families of the four victims in last
night's sinking of an Albanian boat after it collided with an
Italian navy corvette.
</P>
<P>
Italy is willing to coordinate initiatives on the part of the
European Union, the United nations and the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe, Dini wrote to Foreign Minister
Arian Starova.
</P>
<P>
"The initiatives the Italian government has taken and continues
to take to involve the international community aim to solve the
Albanian situation by promoting national conciliation, laying the
groundwork for humanitarian and medical aid, and working toward
rebuilding the country," Dini said.

