<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- China will keep the increase rate of retail price under six
percent and that of consumer price under eight percent this year,
according to the State Council's price control program of 1997.
</P>
<P>
China's retail price index rose 6.1 percent in 1996 and the
consumer price index 8.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman said in Beijing yesterday
that China welcomes and appreciates France's decision that it
will not participate this year in a United Nations human rights
conference motion which will be directed against China's human
rights conditions.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Bank of China said that the bank deposits
surplus in rural credit cooperatives amounted to 879.4 billion
yuan at the end of last year, while that of loans topped 629
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Eighty percent of loans for farmers and 70 percent of loans
for village and township enterprises are provided by rural credit
cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
-- China has preliminarily set up a legal system for the
management of state-owned assets, with three administrative
regulations and 160 rules promulgated.
</P>
<P>
An authority with the National Administrative Bureau of
State-owned Assets (NABSA) said that the legal system, with the
"State-owned Assets Law" at the core, still being drafted,
includes a number of administrative regulations drawn up by the
State Council, the country's highest governing body, and many
rules drafted by the NABSA and some departments.
</P>
<P>
-- Friendship and cooperation are the keystone of Sino-Japanese
relationship, which should not be affected by the existing
problems in bilateral ties, Foreign Minister Qian Qichen told his
Japanese counterpart Ikeda Yukihiko in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
 "Business Weekly of China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China is encouraging several State firms to create a limited
holding company with investment from several businesses, according
to the State Planning Commission's State Information Center (SIC).
</P>
<P>
the government's most crucial task is to establish a modern
managerial system for state companies. It must select more
qualified state firms to participate in a trial operation, SIC
senior economist Chen Mingxing.
</P>
<P>
-- China's financial opening, though gradual and prudent, took
a historical step last week when two overseas banks kicked off the
long-awaited renminbi services in Shanghai Pudong New Zone.
</P>
<P>
The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corp and the Industrial Bank
of Japan opened yuan accounts and loans on thursday after
receiving final approval from the central government.
</P>
<P>
-- To re-capture the ordinary steel products market, China will
take measures this year to prevent dumping from foreign countries,
according to a strategy outlined by the Ministry of Metallurgical
Industry.
</P>
<P>
the industry's domestic market strategy also focuses on long
steel products and finished products used to make cars and oil
pipelines. Minister Liu Qi outlined the plan at the industry's
national working conference.  
</P>
</TEXT>
