<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Villages Have Telephone Access in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- More than 70 percent of the
villages in Fujian Province now have access to telephone service
thanks to the helping hand of the local government.
</P>
<P>
With a government investment of 800 million yuan last year,
some 1,835 villages in the province have installed telephone lines.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, telecommunications developed rapidly in
Fujian's rural areas; the majority of the villages and towns in
the province have been provided with program-controlled telephone
service.
</P>
<P>
But in the countryside, problems such as few subscribers and
poor economic returns have hindered the development of
communications.
</P>
<P>
Some 6,000 villages in the out-of-the-way or economically
undeveloped areas could not have telephone service at the end of
1995.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the provincial government decided to open telephone
service in 1,500 villages each year in a bid to form a complete
telephone network in the province by 1999.
</P>
<P>
The project needs a total investment of about 3.3 billion yuan,
mainly made by local telecommunication departments, and the
provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Optical fibers will be used as the main material of the rural
telephone lines, said an official in charge of the
telecommunications in the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
