<HEADLINE> Romania Beats Liechtenstein in World Cup qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Romania crushed Liechtenstein
8-0 in a World Cup group eight qualifier on Saturday with
Barcelona midfielder Gheorghe Popescu leading the rout with four
goals.
</P>
<P>
Gheorghe Hagi, Viorel Moldovan, Dan Petrescu and Gheorghe
Craioveanu completed the scoring which maintained Romania's 100
per cent record in the group with four wins out of four matches
played and a goal difference of 18-0.
</P>
<P>
Romania could easily have had more goals, going close on at
least another eight occasions against their totally outclassed
opponents who have now lost all five of their qualifiers with a
goal tally of 2-29. At least this score was something of an
improvement on their last outing which ended in an 11-1 loss to
Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
In the end they failed to hit double figures but still chalked
up their biggest win since beating Finland 9-0 in a World Cup
qualifier in Bucharest almost 24 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Liechtenstein's cause was not helped by heavy rain and a muddy
field. But Romania's team, comprising 11 overseas-based players,
totally domintated proceedings to stay on course for a place in
the finals in France next year.
</P>
<P>
Romania are unlikely to have things quite as much their own way
on Wednesday when they face Lithuania but whatever happens then,
the Romanians will stay top of the group as they go into that game
five points clear of second-placed Ireland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
