<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Corporate Bonds in Short Sell in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Corporate bonds met with investor
enthusiasm in southeastern Fujian Province recently, with 200
million yuan-worth of bonds for railway construction sold out in
two hours.
</P>
<P>
The three-year bonds, at an annual interest rate of 11
percent, are jointly guaranteed by the provincial Railway
Construction Development Corporation and the provincial Bureau of
Finance.
</P>
<P>
In the 1,000-yuan denomination, the bonds were offered at more
than 1,000 outlets across the province and will be listed on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange (SSE) after the public offering.
</P>
<P>
An analyst said the buying craze was a result of the bulging
pockets of urban and rural residents, and a lack of new stocks in
the local market.
</P>
<P>
"Besides, the bonds carry a higher interest rate than the state
treasury bonds as well as a solid promise for repayment upon
maturity," said the analyst, pointing to a probable gain in the
bonds' value once listed in the SSE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
