<HEADLINE> Barthe Wins Criterium Cycling First Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Stephane Barthe of France claimed
the opening stage of the Criterium international cycling race
Saturday, a 188km run from Blaye-les-Mines to Rabastens:
</P>
<P>
Barthe, 24, won a sprint finish to edge out Mario Traversoni of
Italy and Frederic Moncassin of France as he completed the stage
in four hours 47 minutes 28 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The peloton was surprised some 15km from the finish when a
stray horse suddenly leapt into their midst around Isle-sur-Tarn
before disappearing from the fray as quickly as it had
materialised.
</P>
<P>
Barthe just pipped Traversoni on the line after the latter had
hit the front to hold off Moncassin's challenge.
</P>
<P>
Both the front two raised their arms aloft in the belief they
had won but a photo-finish gave the Frenchman the verdict for his
first stage win in a major event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
