<HEADLINE> Light Blues Beats Oxford in Boat Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Cambridge beat Oxford in the 143rd
Boat Race to record their fifth successive victory in the famous
event on the Thames here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Cambridge hung on grimly as Oxford threatened to streak ahead
on the Surrey Bend going into the final stages and finally pulled
away to triumph by six seconds.
</P>
<P>
It was Cambridge's 74th win in the 6,800-meter event, their
rivals having won 68 with one tie. 
