<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins WTA Lipton Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Swiss prodigy Martina Hingis
defeated Monica Seles 6-2, 6-1 to win the WTA Lipton Tennis
Championships in Key Biscayne, Florida on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis needed only 44 minutes to defeat the American former
number one and register her 29th consecutive win this year,
collecting 215,000 U.S. dollars in prize money.
</P>
<P>
Hingis beat Seles 6-2, 6-0, last November in the final at
Oakland in their only prior meeting. But Seles was suffering with
a sore shoulder that forced her out of the WTA Championships two
weeks later.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will become the youngest world number one in tennis
history Monday when she replaces injured Steffi Graf atop the WTA
rankings.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss prodigy will be 16 years, six months and one day --
nine months and 18 days younger than the mark set by Seles in
1991. Hingis was ranked 399th three years ago when she joined the
tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
