<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jansher Beats Martin in Squash Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 29 (Xinhua) -- World champion Jansher Khan
regained the Super Series title when he beat Australian Brett
Martin in straight games at Hatfield's Galleria Shopping Center on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It refilled the only important gap in Jansher's trophy cabinet
after his shock defeat to England's Del Harris last year and
should have further boosted the great Pakistani's confidence
before next week's British Open.
</P>
<P>
He will be trying to win the famous tournament for a sixth
successive time, and the manner of Saturday's victory by 9-7, 9-5,
9-2 over the gifted Martin suggested Jansher is a stronger
favourite than he was a couple of weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The crucial moment of the match came at 8-7 in the first game
when Jansher played a clinging little forehand volley drop that
lured Martin into a forehand drive which passed too close to
himself and gave the Pakistani a penalty point.
</P>
<P>
In the second game Jansher was more on top, with Martin
increasing his complaints about the refereeing, and in the third
game it was one way traffic as Jansher took the first eight points
without reply.
</P>
<P>
In the match for the third place, Simon Parke of England beat
Ahmed Barada of Egypt 9-7, 9-2, 5-9, 5-9 and 9-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
